Question 2: Explain the key differences between JavaScript and HTML. Provide examples of situations where
you would use each.

Answer2:
Feature	||  HTML (HyperText Markup Language)     ||	JavaScript
Purpose	||Structures content on a webpage	      ||Adds interactivity and functionality
Type	||      Markup language	                     ||Programming language 
Execution||	  Read by browsers to display content	  ||Runs in the browser's JavaScript engine
Usage Example||	Creating headings, paragraphs, images ||Handling form validation, animations, dynamic updates